data.text:
WOLLESONIC RETURNS TO ROULETTE ON JULY 24 & 25 @ 8:30PM WITH A SURREALISTIC SONIC-VISUAL SPECTACLE BASED ON AN ANCIENT TALE OF PERCEPTION AND AWARENESS FROM HYEMEYOHSTS STORM’S BOOK “SEVEN ARROWS”. THE STORY IS CALLED “JUMPING MOUSE”…….

WOLLESONIC (A SONIC DESIGN LABORATORY FOUNDED BY NEW YORK DRUMMER KENNY WOLLESEN & INSTRUMENT MAKER & DRUMMER DANIEL JODECY) WILL REVEAL THE STORY WITH SOUND & IMAGERY FEATURING ONE-OF-KIND MUSICAL INSTRUMENTS (SOME OF WHICH ARE BUILD ESPECIALLY FOR THESE PERFORMANCES) , PERCUSSION, CHANTS, SUPER-8 FILMS, KALEIDOSCOPIC PROJECTIONS (KNOWN AS ROTORIFICS), HAND-MADE MARIMBAS, MOBILES, MAGIC AND MORE…….

DON’T YOU DARE MISS IT!!!!
